# GBNF grammar for post-tool natural language output (second inference pass)
# Constrains to natural language ONLY — prevents recursive tool calls.
# Allows any characters except sequences beginning with "<|tool_call".
# Uses nested alternation to reject the pattern character by character.

root ::= posttext

posttext ::= (?s:.)*?

# Actually GBNF doesn't support negative lookahead. Let's try a different approach:
# A grammar that matches ANY text, but must not produce <|tool_call|>call:.
# In GBNF, we can still reject the pattern by defining it in a way that the
# grammar engine cannot match it. But GBNF works by filtering tokens — it
# doesn't pre-filter the generated string.
#
# Simplest correct approach: just let post-tool run with standard sampling
# (no grammar) but set max tokens lower. So this file is intentionally empty.
# 
# The tool-call grammar (tool-call.gbnf) is the one that matters.
